Police in Migori are probing an accident where three children were burnt to death in their house at Kodero village in Uriri subcounty on Saturday night. The three, aged 11, 7, and 4 years were on their own after their father Mathews Ochieng' attended to an unknown errand. Area chief Ojwang' Olemo said the children were using a candle which is suspected to have caused the fire. "The man had separated with his wife two months ago following a domestic dispute," the chief said. Police and residents managed to put off the fire. The bodies were taken to Migori Level Four hospital mortuary. Click here for the latest political news